In this lecture, we are going to look at
technologies for on-site blackwater and

2
00:00:08,920 --> 00:00:13,250
greywater management, including the
septic tank and the biogas reactor.

3
00:00:13,270 --> 00:00:17,270
These technologies are based on
anaerobic processes, and I will just

4
00:00:17,270 --> 00:00:18,940
explain what that means.

5
00:00:19,170 --> 00:00:24,300
The word 'anaerobic' describes
biological processes that occur in the

6
00:00:24,300 --> 00:00:26,050
absence of oxygen.

7
00:00:26,050 --> 00:00:30,140
These processes naturally take place in
swamps, marshes, ponds and other

8
00:00:30,150 --> 00:00:34,150
standing water bodies.
They can easily be recognized

9
00:00:34,160 --> 00:00:38,160
by the formation of gas bubbles,
as shown in these beautiful photographs.

10
00:00:38,160 --> 00:00:42,160
The gas is formed, for example, at the
bottom of a pond, where the anaerobic

11
00:00:43,460 --> 00:00:47,460
bacteria decompose carbon-rich organic
substances into methane and carbon dioxide

12
00:00:48,940 --> 00:00:50,470
(also called 'biogas').

13
00:00:50,830 --> 00:00:56,780
The gas bubbles then rise to the surface.
In cold areas, where the lake surfaces

14
00:00:56,810 --> 00:00:59,800
freeze in wintertime, it can
sometimes be observed that

15
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:04,140
the bubbles get trapped below the ice
surface, as shown on the two pictures

16
00:01:04,170 --> 00:01:05,110
