and this one here is a biogas stove.
This technology has the clear benefit that

90
00:06:25,190 --> 00:06:29,190
no energy is required for operation,
but energy is actually produced.

91
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:34,560
A high reduction of organic
matter and particles can be achieved.

92
00:06:35,460 --> 00:06:39,560
The digestate is almost odorless and
still contains all the nutrients, so it

93
00:06:39,570 --> 00:06:44,860
can be used as an excellent fertilizer,
however, the agricultural application

94
00:06:44,860 --> 00:06:49,620
has to be done correctly and carefully
because the digestate may still contain

95
00:06:49,620 --> 00:06:53,660
some pathogens.
This technology has many benefits

96
00:06:53,660 --> 00:06:57,860
but its success depends on correct
implementation by experts, proper

97
00:06:57,860 --> 00:07:01,100
operation and regular maintenance.

98
00:07:01,140 --> 00:07:05,140
We have seen that there are several
anaerobic technologies that are robust

99
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:08,890
and easy to operate for on-site
treatment of blackwater and greywater.

100
00:07:09,910 --> 00:07:12,620
I want you to remember
two things from this module:

101
00:07:12,740 --> 00:07:17,370
First - septic tanks can be a good
solution but it is important that the

102
00:07:17,370 --> 00:07:21,680
effluent is properly disposed of and
that the sludge is regularly removed.

103
00:07:22,700 --> 00:07:26,410
The second thing that I want you to
remember is that the biogas reactor

104
00:07:26,410 --> 00:07:31,520
can be an attractive technology, but the
economic benefits do not mean that it is

105
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:35,740
always automatically successful.
Whether or not the initial investment

106
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:39,800
costs can be recovered will depend on
the correct design and implementation

107
00:07:40,610 --> 00:07:42,580
and their motivated operator.
